[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 13 points so he must open. He has five \Hs so he 
should open 1\H.

SOUTH, with 14 points and four \Hs knows there are 
enough points for a game contract and at least nine \Hs between 
the partners. She who KNOWS, GOES, so SOUTH bids 4\H.

This is similar to Deal 13.}

