[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH passes to start with since he only has 9 points.

SOUTH naturally opens 1\S with her 13 point, 5-card \S suit hand.

NORTH might now make a Limit Raise since his hand is now worth 11 points because of the 
two doubletons. However, with six trumps he should jump all the way to 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:AQ9753.Q7.AK3.K2 K4.8643.J752.A84 JT82.K52.86.Q763 6.AJT9.QT94.JT95"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1S pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
