[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 20 points, but with a 5-card Major opens 1\H rather than 2NT.

SOUTH barely has enough points for a response, but she does have four \Hs. 
So she responds 2\H.

NORTH adds SOUTH's 6 to his 20 and bids the game, 4\H.}

